<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-12-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-12-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1472" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1472">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.00.2166.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 70.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-12-18">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 18, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your No. 68,
                            of July 31, 1912, transmitting correspondence relating to the
                            revolutionary attempt of General Luis Mena, of July 29, 1912.</p>
                        <p>Your action in obtaining an interview with General Mena in which you
                            communicated to him President Díaz’s offer of amnesty on condition that
                            he resign as Minister of War, and in obtaining from General Mena and the
                            General commanding the Government forces letters in which they agreed to
                            carry out such an arrangement, which was afterward violated by Mena, is
                            approved by the Department.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>